VALUES ('C1_U4_B2_I1', 'ingles-c1-U4', 2, 'word_formation', 'Fill in the gaps with the correct form of the word provided in parentheses.', '{"prompt_es":"Fill in the gaps with the correct form of the word provided in parentheses.","mastery_tag":"vocabulary:c1-nuanced","main_text":"Effective communication often requires a deep understanding of (1)___ (NUANCE) in language. To express (2)___ (PRECISE) thoughts, one must choose words with care. A word’s (3)___ (CONNOTATE) can change its meaning entirely, making it essential to grasp subtleties. Moreover, (4)___ (SOPHISTICATE) language can enhance the (5)___ (EFFECT) of a message when used appropriately.","correct_answer":["NUANCES","PRECISION","CONNOTATION","SOPHISTICATION","EFFECTIVENESS"],"example":"NUANCE, PRECISE, CONNOTATE, SOPHISTICATE, EFFECT","explanation":"(1) undefined\n(2) undefined\n(3) undefined\n(4) undefined\n(5) undefined"}')
